        <updateDate>2017-03-01T21:06:21Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><strong>Student Loan Opportunity Act of 201</strong><b>7</b></p> <p>This bill amends the Internal Revenue Code, with respect to tax-exempt private activity bond financing, to: (1) eliminate a provision that restricts nonprofit scholarship funding corporations that acquire student loan notes to notes incurred under the Higher Education Act of 1965 (thus allowing such corporations to access tax-exempt financing for other types of student loans), and (2) expand the operations of such corporations to include performing student assistance related activities.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
